Shadow given permanent form, the Umbral are humanoids whose bodies incorporated
anti-light over generations of habitation in zones adjacent to the Black Sun Shard.
Their substance is as much darkness as flesh: partially insubstantial, difficult to
perceive clearly, and healing most efficiently in shadow rather than light. The
Gloamvault beneath Midgaard is their most ancient habitation — the city was built
above them, not the other way around. They maintain shadow-archives whose parallel
records document what the human institutions above them would rather suppress, and
both Midgaard's factions treat them as simultaneously a resource and a threat.
